    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6992965>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Phylogeny of Synergini. Maximum likelihood (ML) tree resulting from the analysis of combined data of partial sequences of COI, Cytb, 28S D2 and 28S D3. Bootstrap (BS) and posterior probability (PP) values are depicted next to respective nodes, indicating BS in ML method and PPs in Bayesian inference (BI) method (BS/PP). When a clade position is not congruent or clades are recovered in a polytomy in the BI tree, PPs values are presented as ‘--’. Host-plant associations and distribution are shown next to species names by abbreviations and coloured dots.Type species are pointed out with ‘*’ and highlighted in bold. A, Rhoophilus loewi [Simon van Noort (Iziko Museums of South Africa), CC0]; B, Synergus magnificus [Matthew Buffington (USNM), sent to IL-V]; C, Synergus pseudofilicornis (IL-V); D, Saphonecrus connatus [Arnstein" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6992965/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

